{{對女性的暴力}}
{{性與法律}}

'''-{zh-cn:残割女性生殖器;zh-hk:殘割女性生殖器;zh-tw:女陰殘割}-'''（{{lang|en|Female genital mutilation}}，FGM），又稱為'''女性生殖器切割'''（female genital cutting，FGC），或'''女性割禮'''（female circumcision）。[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]將其定義為「包括所有涉及为非医学原因，部分或全部切除[[女性外生殖器|女性外生殖器]]，或对女性生殖器官造成其它伤害的程序」<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/topics/fgm/overview/zh/|title=世界卫生组织 {{!}} 女性生殖器切割的分类|website=www.who.int|access-date=2016-03-27|archive-date=2020-07-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200715013736/https://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/topics/fgm/overview/zh/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="WHO12">[https://web.archive.org/web/20151107115822/http://www.un.org/zh/events/femalegenitalmutilationday/ "Classification of female genital mutilation"], World Health Organization, 2013 (hereafter WHO 2013).</ref>。在[[撒哈拉以南非洲|撒哈拉以南]]、[[北非|北非]]及[[中東|中東]]等地區，許多{{le|非洲種族|Ethnic groups of Africa|族群}}將女陰殘割視為傳統[[習俗|習俗]]的一部分，目前已知有27個國家境內具有這種風俗<ref>有關殘割、麻醉，請參見：[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 2, 44–46。女陰殘割盛行地區報告，請參見：[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGMC_2016_brochure_final_UNICEF_SPREAD.pdf UNICEF 2016] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGMC_2016_brochure_final_UNICEF_SPREAD.pdf |date=20170210071422 }}, p. 2.</ref>。每個地區進行女陰殘割的時間不同，有的是在出生後幾天，有的則是到[[青春期|青春期]]才進行。這27個國家中，當中只有一半的國家能夠取得統計數據。根據這些資料顯示，大多數的女孩在5歲之前就會進行女陰殘割<ref name=UNICEF2013/>{{rp|50}}。

不同民族之間的執行過程不盡相同，有些切除部分[[陰蒂|陰蒂]]和[[陰蒂包皮|陰蒂包皮]]，也有的切除整個陰蒂和[[小陰唇|小陰唇]]；甚至將大小陰唇全部切除，使[[陰道|陰道]]癒合，俗稱{{le|鎖陰手術|Infibulation}}，[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]（WHO）則稱為「第三型女陰殘割」。被鎖陰後的女性下體僅剩下一個小孔，讓[[尿液|尿液]]和[[經血|經血]]排除，直到要進行[[性交|性交]]及生育時才再次將陰道口打開。女陰殘割所造成的影響因操作程序不同而有所差異，包含反覆感染、[[囊腫|囊腫]]、[[不孕症|不孕症]]、生產時併發症及致命性出血<ref name="Abdulcadira2011">Jasmine Abdulcadira, et al., [http://www.smw.ch/content/smw-2011-13137/ "Care of women with female genital mutilation/cutting"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.smw.ch/content/smw-2011-13137/ |date=20160718085718 }}, ''Swiss Medical Weekly'', 6(14), January 2011. {{doi|10.4414/smw.2011.13137}} PMID 21213149</ref>。目前女陰殘割並沒有任何已知的醫療助益<ref name="WHO2014health2">[http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs241/en/ "Female genital mutilation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs241/en/ |date=20180402081316 }}, Geneva: World Health Organization, February 2016.</ref>。

女陰殘割是女性的性控制，具有[[性別不平等|性別不平等]]的意味。執行女陰殘割的地區將此舉視作純潔、端莊與美麗的象徵，且認為女陰殘割可以幫助女性保守對丈夫的忠貞<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.appledaily.com.tw/realtimenews/article/new/20150703/641013/ |title=肯亞女行割禮為守貞 「割掉就不會找男人」 蘋果日報 2015/7/3 |accessdate=2015-12-25 |archive-date=2015-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225175607/http://www.appledaily.com.tw/realtimenews/article/new/20150703/641013/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。手術通常由家族中的女性成員操作，因為她們認為沒有進行女陰殘割會使她們的女兒或孫女遭受[[社會排斥|社會排斥]]{{efn|UNICEF 2013：「在當地，（居民）認為這是一項社會義務。且他們大多廣泛認為，如果他們（的家人）沒有做，必須付出包含社會排斥、批評、嘲笑、羞辱，或在擇偶時被視為缺陷者。」<ref name=UNICEF2013/>{{rp|15}}{{pb}}
{{le|Nahid Toubia|Nahid Toubia|Nahid F. Toubia}}, Eiman Hussein Sharief, 2003: "One of the great achievements of the past decade in the field of FGM is the shift in emphasis from the concern over the harmful physical effects it causes to understanding this act as a social phenomenon resulting from a gender definition of women's roles, in particular their sexual and reproductive roles. This shift in emphasis has helped redefine the issues from a clinical disease model (hence the terminology of eradication prevalent in the literature) to a problem resulting from the use of culture to protect social dominance over women's bodies by the patriarchal hierarchy. Understanding the operative mechanisms of patriarchal dominance must also include understanding how women, particularly older married women, are important keepers of that social hegemony."<ref>{{tsl|en|Nahid Toubia||Nahid F. Toubia}}, Eiman Hussein Sharief, [http://www.ijgo.org/article/S0020-7292%2803%2900229-7/fulltext "Female genital mutilation: have we made progress?"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ijgo.org/article/S0020-7292%2803%2900229-7/fulltext |date=20170101060238 }}, ''International Journal of Gynecology & Obstetrics'', 82(3), September 2003, pp. 251–261. {{doi|10.1016/S0020-7292(03)00229-7}} PMID 14499972</ref>}}。截至2016年，逾2億名女性已接受過FGM，並分布於30個國家。[[联合国人口基金|联合国人口基金]]預估，截至2010年，20%的已殘割人口曾經經歷過鎖陰手術。此類習俗主要分布於北非，特別是[[吉布地|吉布地]]、[[厄利垂亞|厄利垂亞]]、[[索馬利亞|索馬利亞]]和[[蘇丹|蘇丹]]<ref name=UNFPATypeIIIestimate/><ref name="Yoder2008p13"/>。

在上述具有女陰殘割習俗的國家，大多明令立法禁止這類風俗，但成效不彰。自從1970年代起，各國紛紛說服人們廢止它。2012年，[[聯合國大會|聯合國大會]]認定女陰殘割違反人權<ref name=UN/>。但並非無人反對干預此習俗，特別是[[人類學|人類學家]]。{{le|埃里克·西爾弗曼|Eric Silverman}}表示，女陰殘割已經成為[[人類學|人類學]]的一項中心道德議題，因其涉及[[文化相對論|文化相對論]]、人權的普世性和寬容性等難題<ref name="Silverman2004">{{tsl|en|Eric Silverman|埃里克·西爾弗曼|Eric K. Silverman}}, "Anthropology and Circumcision," ''Annual Review of Anthropology'', 33, 2004, pp. 419–445. {{jstor|25064860}}</ref>{{rp|420, 427}}。

==詞源==
===英文===
[[File:Samburu_female_circumcision_ceremony,_Kenya.jpg|thumb]][[萊基皮亞郡|萊基皮亞高原]]的[[桑布鲁人|桑布鲁人]]在進行女性割禮，攝於2004年。]]

1980年以前，切除女性生殖器的習俗通常被稱為“{{lang|en|female circumcision}}”（女性割禮），暗示其與[[割禮|男性割禮]]的相似性<ref>Martha Nussbaum, ''Sex and Social Justice'', New York: Oxford University Press, 1999, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=7zoaKIolT9oC&pg=PA119 119] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=7zoaKIolT9oC&pg=PA119 |date=20130921055430 }}.</ref>。1929年，在[[蘇格蘭長老會|蘇格蘭長老會]]傳教士{{le|馬里昂·史蒂文森|Marion Scott Stevenson}}領導之下，{{le|肯亞宣教協會|Kenya Missionary Council}}開始將此習俗視為對女性的一種性傷害<ref>James Karanja, ''The Missionary Movement in Colonial Kenya: The Foundation of Africa Inland Church'', Göttingen: Cuvillier Verlag, 2009, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=F1ezIgyomGIC&pg=PA93 93] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=F1ezIgyomGIC&pg=PA93 |date=20170908222703 }}, n. 631.</ref>。到了1970年代，將FGM視為性傷害的人數增加<ref>[http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf "Eliminating Female genital mutilation: An Interagency Statement"] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, New York: World Health Organization, 2008 (hereafter WHO 2008), p. 22.</ref>。人類學家羅斯·歐德菲爾德·海耶斯（Rose Oldfield Hayes）在1975年的一篇論文標題中首次使用了「{{lang|en|female genital mutilation}}」（女陰殘割）這個名词；1979年，奧地利裔美籍學者{{le|弗蘭·霍斯肯|Fran Hosken}}在她的重要論文《霍斯肯報告：女性生殖器及性器官殘割》（''The Hosken Report: Genital and Sexual Mutilation of Females''）中，確立了「{{lang|en|female genital mutilation}}」這個名词。{{efn|Claire C. Robertson, Professor of History and Women's Studies at The Ohio State University, 2002: "The ''Hosken Report'' is the single most influential document responsible for raising consciousness of FGC."<ref>Claire C. Robertson, "Getting beyond the Ew! Factor: Rethinking U.S. Approaches to African Female Genital Cutting," in Stanlie M. James and Claire C. Robertson (eds.), ''Genital Cutting and Transnational Sisterhood'', Urbana: University of Illinois Press, 2002 (pp. 54–86), p. 60.{{pb}}
Fran Hosken, ''The Hosken Report: Genital and Sexual Mutilation of Females'', Lexington: Women's International Network, 1994 [1979].</ref>}}

其後，{{le|泛非洲影響婦女及兒童的傳統醫療實務協會|Inter-African Committee on Traditional Practices Affecting the Health of Women and Children}}於1990年始用「{{lang|en|female genital mutilation}}」這個詞彙<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 6–7.</ref>；而在1997年4月，世界衛生組織、[[聯合國兒童基金會|聯合國兒童基金會]]（UNICEF），和[[联合国人口基金|联合国人口基金]]（UNFPA）同樣宣布採用「{{lang|en|female genital mutilation}}」一詞為描述女性割禮的術語，其他醫療人士同時也使用包括「{{lang|en|female genital cutting}}」（女性生殖器切割）之同義詞彙稱之<ref>[http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, pp. 4, 22.</ref>。

===其他語言===
在具有女性割禮盛行的地方，則對於此習俗有許多稱呼<ref name="UNICEF2013p48/50terms"/>，通常與純潔的意象有關。比如說，[[阿拉伯語|阿拉伯語]]男性割禮（''tahur''）和女性割禮（''tahara''）中，帶有「t-h-r」的字根，而這類字根則通常帶有純潔的意思<ref>Fadwa El Guindi, "Had ''This'' Been Your Face, Would You Leave It as Is?" in Rogaia Mustafa Abusharaf (ed.), ''Female Circumcision: Multicultural Perspectives'', Philadelphia: University of Pennsylvania Press, 2007, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA30 30] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA30 |date=20170908222703 }}.</ref>。在[[马里|马里]]的[[班巴拉語|班巴拉語]]中，男性或女性割禮皆稱為「''{{lang|bm|bolokoli}}''」，意指「洗淨雙手」。東奈及利亞的[[伊博語|伊博語]]則將其稱為「''{{lang|ig|isa aru}}''」或「''{{lang|ig|iwu aru}}''」，則為「沐浴」之意<ref>Chantal Zabus, "The Excised Body in African Texts and Contexts," in Merete Falck Borch (ed.), ''Bodies and Voices: The Force-field of Representation and Discourse in Colonial and Postcolonial Studies'', New York: Rodopi, 2008, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=xZmWF3qxHo4C&pg=PA47 47] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=xZmWF3qxHo4C&pg=PA47 |date=20170908222703 }}.<p>
For "a young woman must 'have her bath' before she has a baby," Chantal Zabus, "'Writing with an Accent': From Early Decolonization to Contemporary Gender Issues in the African Novel in French, English, and Arabic," in Simona Bertacco (ed.), ''Language and Translation in Postcolonial Literatures'', New York: Routledge, 2013, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=NCJiAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA40&lpg=PA40 40] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=NCJiAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA40&lpg=PA40 |date=20170908222703 }}.</ref>。

聖行割禮通常又稱為陰蒂切除術，但也用於更極端的形式；[[聖行|聖行]]阿拉伯語中意為「行為」、「道路」，也意指傳統的[[穆罕默德|穆罕默德]]，但過程其實和伊斯蘭教無關<ref>Ibrahim Lethome Asmani, Maryam Sheikh Abdi, [http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/De-linking%20FGM%20from%20Islam%20final%20report.pdf "De-linking Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting from Islam"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/De-linking%20FGM%20from%20Islam%20final%20report.pdf |date=20170221230457 }}, USAID/UNFPA, 2008, p. 3.<p>

That ''sunna'' can refer to more severe forms, [[Ellen_Gruenbaum|Ellen Gruenbaum]], ''The Female Circumcision Controversy: An Anthropological Perspective'', Philadelphia: University of Pennsylvania Press, 2001, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=JOXmOLBd4E4C&pg=PA2 2].</ref>。{{le|鎖陰手術|Infibulation}}一詞的拉丁文「infibulation」源自於扣環（fibula）。據說古羅馬時期，為避免奴隸性交，會使用扣環緊扣於他們的包皮或陰唇<ref name=Kouba1985pp96-97>Leonard J. Kouba, Judith Muasher, [http://www.jstor.org/stable/524569 "Female Circumcision in Africa: An Overview"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/524569 |date=20210108162601 }}, ''African Studies Review'', 28(1), March 1985 (pp. 95–110), pp. 96–97.</ref>，蘇丹和埃及蘇丹人將女性鎖陰手術稱為「法老的割禮」<ref name=Kouba1985pp96-97/>，但古埃及僅有男性有割禮，女性並無此習俗<ref>{{cite web|author1=Rossella Lorenzi|title=How Did Female Genital Mutilation Begin?|website=How Did Female Genital Mutilation Begin?|accessdate=2015-11-05}}</ref>。索馬利亞則稱之為「qodob」意指「縫合」<ref>[[Raqiya_Haji_Dualeh_Abdalla|Raqiya D. Abdalla]], {{" '}}My Grandmother Called it the Three Feminine Sorrows': The Struggle of Women Against Female Circumcision in Somalia," in Abusharaf 2007, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA190 190] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA190 |date=20170908222703 }}.</ref>。

==割禮進行方式==
[[File:Clitoris_Anatomy.svg|lang=zh]]構造圖，包含了[[陰蒂|陰蒂]]、[[陰蒂海綿體|陰蒂海綿體]]、[[前庭球|前庭球]]、以及[[陰蒂腳|陰蒂腳]]。]]

女性割禮通常由女生家中的傳統割禮師執行。割禮師通常是較老的女性，但在有些社區，男性[[理髮師|理髮師]]兼任健康工作者，也會負責執行這項手術<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 42–44 and Table 5, p. 181 (for cutters), p. 46 (for home and anaesthesia).</ref>{{efn|UNICEF 2005: "The large majority of girls and women are cut by a traditional practitioner, a category which includes local specialists (cutters or ''exciseuses''), traditional birth attendants and, generally, older members of the community, usually women. This is true for over 80 percent of the girls who undergo the practice in Benin, Burkina Faso, Côte d'Ivoire, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Guinea, Mali, Niger, Tanzania and Yemen. In most countries, medical personnel, including doctors, nurses and certified midwives, are not widely involved in the practice."}}<ref>Michael Miller and Francesca Moneti, [http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf ''Changing a harmful social convention: Female genital cutting/mutilation''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf |date=20180928122738 }}, Florence: UNICEF Innocenti Research Centre, 2005, p. 7.</ref>。在埃及、蘇丹和肯亞，通常會有專業的醫療人士陪同。根據一項2008年的調查，在埃及77%的女性割禮會由專業醫療人士陪同，通常是內科醫生<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 43–45.</ref>。

當由傳統割禮師執行儀式時，很有可能是使用沒有消毒的切割器具，包括刀子、雷射、剪刀、玻璃、磨利的石頭和指甲<ref name=Kelly2005p491>Elizabeth Kelly, Paula J. Adams Hillard, [http://journals.lww.com/co-obgyn/Abstract/2005/10000/Female_genital_mutilation.9.aspx "Female genital mutilation"] {{Wayback|url=http://journals.lww.com/co-obgyn/Abstract/2005/10000/Female_genital_mutilation.9.aspx |date=20170909054405 }}, ''Current Opinion in Obstetrics & Gynecology'', 17(5), October 2005 (pp. 490–494), p. 491. {{PMID|16141763}}</ref>。一位[[烏干達|烏干達]]的護士曾在2007年的《[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|刺胳針]]》（''The Lancet''）說，一位割禮師可能會同時用同一把刀，為30位女性執行這個儀式<ref>Wairagala Wakabi, [http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(07)60508-X/fulltext "Africa battles to make female genital mutilation history"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(07)60508-X/fulltext |date=20130514171022 }}, ''The Lancet'', 369 (9567), 31 March 2007, pp. 1069–1070. {{PMID|17405200}} {{doi|10.1016/S0140-6736(07)60508-X}}</ref>。手術過程可能會進行[[全身麻醉|全身麻醉]]或是[[局部麻醉|局部麻醉]]，有時甚至不進行任何麻醉，取決於專業醫療人士的判斷和參與程度。曾有1995年的報導指出，在埃及，60%的情況會進行局部麻醉，13%全身麻醉，而25%完全不進行任何麻醉<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 46 (two percent were missing/don't know).</ref>。

==殘割的種類==
===分類法===
[[File:FGC_Types.svg|right]]
1997年4月，[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]（WHO）、[[联合国儿童基金会|联合国儿童基金会]]（UNICEF）和[[联合国人口基金|联合国人口基金]]（UNFPA）發表了一份聯合聲明，明確定義了「女性殘割」的內容：「無論是因文化還是其他非治療性的原因，凡是涉及部分切除、全部切除女性外生殖器，或是其他傷害女性生殖器官的步驟流程，皆被歸類於『女性殘割』」<ref>[http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, p. 4.</ref>。

而「女性殘割」的步驟根據不同的族群以及不同的醫療從事人員也會有所不同。 1998年在尼日爾的調查顯示，當女性受訪者被問及其自身所遭遇的「女性殘割」過程，其回答的內容超過50種不同的類型<ref name="UNICEF2013p48/50terms">[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 48.</ref>。然而，在受訪者回答其所遭遇的「女性殘割」類型，甚至是否曾經遭遇這樣簡單的問題，由於語言的隔閡，使得調查研究的數據可靠性產生質疑。有些研究甚至認為這些受訪者的受訪內容其可信度是不可靠的。而在2003年迦納的研究指出，在1995年約有4%的受訪女性不曾遭受「女性殘割」，然而在2000年，這一群女性中其中有 11 % 的受訪者，也遭受了「女性殘割」。在坦桑尼亞的研究中，有 66 %的受訪女性是曾遭受「女性殘割」，但在實際的體檢結果，卻證實了其中有73%的女性曾遭受「女性殘割」<ref>P. Stanley Yoder, Shanxiao Wang, Elise Johansen, [http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1728-4465.2013.00352.x/abstract "Estimates of Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting in 27 African Countries and Yemen"] {{Wayback|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1728-4465.2013.00352.x/abstract |date=20171102130836 }}, ''Studies in Family Planning'', 44(2), June 2013 (pp. 189–204), p. 190. {{PMID|23720002}} {{doi|10.1111/j.1728-4465.2013.00352.x}}<p>
Elizabeth F. Jackson, et al., "Inconsistent reporting of female genital cutting status in northern Ghana: Explanatory factors and analytical consequences," ''Studies in Family Planning'', 34(3), 2003, pp. 200–210. {{PMID|14558322}}<p>
Elise Klouman, Rachel Manongi, Knut-Inge Klepp, [http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-3156.2004.01350.x/full "Self-reported and observed female genital cutting in rural Tanzania: Associated demographic factors, HIV and sexually transmitted infections"] {{Wayback|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-3156.2004.01350.x/full |date=20170909052659 }}, ''Tropical Medicine and International Health'' 10(1), 2005, pp. 105–115. {{PMID|15655020}} {{doi|10.1111/j.1365-3156.2004.01350.x}}<p>
In Sudan in 2006, a significant percentage of infibulated women and girls reported a less severe type. See Susan Elmusharaf, Nagla Elhadi, Lars Almroth, [http://www.bmj.com/content/333/7559/124.full "Reliability of self reported form of female genital mutilation and WHO classification: cross sectional study"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bmj.com/content/333/7559/124.full |date=20171114094427 }}, ''British Medical Journal'', 332(7559), 27 June 2006. {{PMID|16803943}} {{PMC|1502195}} {{doi|10.1136/bmj.38873.649074.55}}</ref>。
而給予受訪者的標準問卷問題內容如下：
#切割，但無肉體組織被移除 （意即穿刺，或象徵性的割禮）；
#切割，而有一部分的組織被移除
#完全縫合密閉
#其他不確定或是未知的類型{{efn|UNICEF 2013: "These categories do not fully match the WHO typology. ''Cut, no flesh removed'' describes a practice known as nicking or pricking, which currently is categorized as Type IV. ''Cut, some flesh removed'' corresponds to Type I (clitoridectomy) and Type II (excision) combined. And ''sewn closed'' corresponds to Type III, infibulation."<ref name="UNICEF2013p48/50terms"/>}}

大多數的步驟流程皆被歸類於「切割，有部分的組織被移除」，其中還涉及完全的移除或是部分的移除女性陰蒂頭<ref name=Yoder2013p189TypeI>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 47, Table 5.2; 
[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 Yoder, Wang and Johansen, 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 |date=20171019061100 }}, p. 189.</ref>。

===世界衛生組織分類第一型與第二型===

世界衛生組織目前根據組織被移除的多寡，將女性割禮很詳盡地歸類為類型I - III，而類型 III 指的是「完全縫合密閉」。另外，類型 IV則是對於象徵性的割禮與其他雜項步驟流程進行描述<ref>[http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/topics/fgm/overview/en/ WHO 2014] {{Wayback|url=http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/topics/fgm/overview/en/ |date=20190921071821 }}; [http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, p. 4, and Annex 2, p. 24, for Types I–IV; Annex 2, pp. 23–28, for a more detailed discussion.</ref>。

;類型 I 又可細分為Ia與Ib兩細項：

*Ia：切除[[陰蒂包皮|陰蒂包皮]]（很少單獨執行切除）{{efn|"[There is a] common tendency to describe Type I as removal of the prepuce, whereas this has not been documented as a traditional form of female genital mutilation. However, in some countries, medicalized female genital mutilation can include removal of the prepuce only (Type Ia) (Thabet and Thabet, 2003), but this form appears to be relatively rare (Satti et al, 2006). Almost all known forms of female genital mutilation that remove tissue from the clitoris also cut all or part of the clitoral glans itself."<ref>[http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, p. 25. Also see [[Nahid_Toubia|Nahid Toubia]], [http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199409153311106 "Female Circumcision as a Public Health Issue"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199409153311106 |date=20190610134401 }}, ''The New England Journal of Medicine'', 331(11), 1994, pp. 712–716. {{PMID|8058079}} {{doi|10.1056/NEJM199409153311106}}<p>

Carol R. Horowitz, J. Carey Jackson, Mamae Teklemariam, [http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199409153311106#t=letters "Female Circumcision" (letters)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199409153311106#t=letters |date=20190610134401 }}, ''The New England Journal of Medicine'', 332, 19 January 1995, pp. 188–190; Toubia's [http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199409153311106#t=letters reply] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJM199409153311106#t=letters |date=20190610134401 }}. {{doi|10.1056/NEJM199501193320313}}</ref>}}

*Ib：即陰蒂切除術，此類型較1為普遍。即部分或是完全的切除陰蒂頭與陰蒂包皮。Susan與Nahid Toubia曾在論述中提及：「陰蒂頭被以拇指和食指捏著拉出來，並以尖銳的物品切下。」<ref>Susan Izett, Nahid Toubia, [https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053613/https://apps.who.int/dsa/cat98/fgmbook.htm ''Female Genital Mutilation: An Overview''], World Health Organization, 1998.</ref>
