女陰殘割的盛行區域位於非洲，東迄索馬利亞，西至[[塞內加爾|塞內加爾]]，南至[[坦尚尼亞|坦尚尼亞]]、北至[[埃及|埃及]]。政治科學家{{le|Gerry Mackie|Gerry Mackie}}稱此區域為「令人感興趣的連續區」（{{lang|en|intriguingly contiguous}}）<ref>Gerry Mackie, John LeJeune, [https://web.archive.org/web/20131014151512/http://www.polisci.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/UNICEF.pdf "Social Dynamics of Abandonment of Harmful Practices: A New Look at the Theory"], Innocenti Working Paper No. 2008-XXX, UNICEF Innocenti Research Centre, 2008, p. 5.</ref>。{{As of|2014年}}，29個盛行國家中，已有1.3億名女性已經接受過女陰殘割。預估到2050年，此數字會隨人口增加而上升至2億{{efn|聯合國兒童基金會2014年報告：「如果現在到2050年之間沒有任何減緩，從2013年每年有360萬女童受到割禮的數量將會成長到2050年的660萬。但如果在過去三十年的不斷成長的數率有所維持，受影響的女童數目將會從現在的每年360萬增加到2050年的410萬。」<p>「不論是上面兩種的哪一個情境，受到女性割禮的兒童與成人將會因為人口成長的關係持續增加。如果什麼都不做，受影響的女童與成人的數量將會從現在的1億3千3百萬成長到2015年的3億2千5百萬人。然而，如果現在的成果有維持住，現在受影響的1億3千3百萬到2050年將會有1億9千6百萬人，幾乎1億3千萬的女童將會免於這場對於其人權的重大侵犯。」<p>
（英文原文）UNICEF 2014: "If there is no reduction in the practice between now and 2050, the number of girls cut each year will grow from 3.6 million in 2013 to 6.6 million in 2050. But if the rate of progress achieved over the last 30 years is maintained, the number of girls affected annually will go from 3.6 million today to 4.1 million in 2050.<p>"In either scenario, the total number of girls and women cut will continue to increase due to population growth. If nothing is done, the number of girls and women affected will grow from 133 million today to 325 million in 2050. However, if the progress made so far is sustained, the number will grow from 133 million to 196 million in 2050, and almost 130 million girls will be spared this grave assault to their human rights."<ref>[http://data.unicef.org/corecode/uploads/document6/uploaded_pdfs/corecode/FGM-C-Brochure-7_15-Final-LR_167.pdf UNICEF 2014] {{Wayback|url=http://data.unicef.org/corecode/uploads/document6/uploaded_pdfs/corecode/FGM-C-Brochure-7_15-Final-LR_167.pdf |date=20141021224539 }}, p. 3.</ref>}}。

2013年時埃及、衣索比亞和奈及利亞有最多的女性與女孩遭遇女陰殘割，估計分別是2720萬人、2380萬人以及1990萬人<ref>UNICEF 2013, p. 2.</ref>（埃及於2007將女陰殘割視為違法行為、衣索比亞在2004年、奈及利亞則是在2015年）<ref>[http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf UNFPA–UNICEF 2012] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf |date=20180316152947 }}, p. 12.</ref><ref name=Egyptban>[http://egypt.unfpa.org/english/fgmStaticpages/3f54a0c6-f088-4bec-8671-5e9421d2adee/National_Legislations_Decrees_and_Statements_banning_fgm.aspx "National Legislation, Decrees and Statements Banning FGM/C"] {{Wayback|url=http://egypt.unfpa.org/english/fgmStaticpages/3f54a0c6-f088-4bec-8671-5e9421d2adee/National_Legislations_Decrees_and_Statements_banning_fgm.aspx |date=20150512150810 }}, UNFPA Egypt.</ref><ref name=Nigeriaban>Alexandra Topping, [http://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/may/29/outlawing-fgm-nigeria-hugely-important-precedent-say-campaigners "Nigeria's female genital mutilation ban is important precedent, say campaigners"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/may/29/outlawing-fgm-nigeria-hugely-important-precedent-say-campaigners |date=20210129045546 }}, ''The Guardian'', 29 May 2015.</ref>。2014年，女陰殘割在[[南撒哈拉|南撒哈拉]]地區成年女性[[患病率|盛行率]]為39%，對於14歲以下的女孩，盛行率為17%。在[[西非|西非]]與[[南非|南非]]這個比例分別是44%與14%，[[西非|西非]]與[[中非共和国|中非]]為31%與17%<ref name=UNICEF2015table9/>。

上述的資料是由{{le|人口與健康調查組織|Demographic and Health Surveys}}（DHS）的家戶調查而來，是由Macro International所提供，資金來源主要是來自[[美国国际开发署|美国国际开发署]]及{{le|多指標集調查組織|Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys}}提供，由[[聯合國兒童基金會|聯合國兒童基金會]]提供的技術及財務支援<ref name=Yoder2013p190>[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 Yoder, Wang and Johansen, 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 |date=20171019061100 }}, p. 190.</ref>。調查是在非洲、亞洲及拉丁美洲等地進行，自1984年及1995年進行，約每五年進行一次<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, Box 1.1, p. 4.</ref><ref>[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 Yoder, Wang and Johansen, 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 |date=20171019061100 }}, p. 190; [http://www.dhsprogram.com/What-We-Do/Survey-Types/DHS.cfm "DHS overview"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dhsprogram.com/What-We-Do/Survey-Types/DHS.cfm |date=20141016202457 }}, Demographic and Health Surveys; [http://www.childinfo.org/mics5_questionnaire.html "Questionnaires and Indicator List"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.childinfo.org/mics5_questionnaire.html |date=20190603024658 }}, Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys, UNICEF.</ref>。

第一份有關女陰殘割的調查是1989年至1990年由人口與健康調查組織（DHS）在北蘇丹進行的調查，第一份估計女陰殘割盛行率的出版物是1997年由Macro International的Dara Carr製作，根據七個國家的DHS資料整理而得<ref>[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 Yoder, Wang and Johansen, 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 |date=20171019061100 }}, p. 191; Dara Carr, ''Female genital cutting: Findings from the Demographic and Health Surveys program'', Calverton, MD: Macro International Inc., 1997.</ref>。聯合國兒童基金會2013年根據70份調查所得的報告，指出女陰殘割集中在非洲的27個國家、葉門及伊拉克的庫德族<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 3, 5.</ref>，在這些國家中有1.33億位女性進行了女陰殘割<ref name=133million>[http://data.unicef.org/corecode/uploads/document6/uploaded_pdfs/corecode/FGM-C-Brochure-7_15-Final-LR_167.pdf ''Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting: What Might the Future Hold?''] {{Wayback|url=http://data.unicef.org/corecode/uploads/document6/uploaded_pdfs/corecode/FGM-C-Brochure-7_15-Final-LR_167.pdf |date=20141021224539 }}, New York: UNICEF, 22 July 2014 (hereafter UNICEF 2014), pp. 3, 6.</ref>。

在上述29個國家以外，在印度、阿聯、以色列的{{le|內蓋夫貝都因人|Negev Bedouin|貝都因人}}有女陰殘割的記錄，在哥倫比亞、剛果、阿曼、秘魯及斯里蘭卡也有出現過，但不常見<ref>[http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, pp. 29–30.</ref>。在約旦、沙烏地阿拉伯、印尼及馬來西亞以及澳洲、紐西蘭、歐洲、斯堪的納維亞、美國及加拿大的移民群體也有這類的情形{{efn|UNICEF 2014: "Although no nationally representative data on FGM/C are available for countries including Colombia, Jordan, Oman, Saudi Arabia and parts of Indonesia and Malaysia, evidence suggests that the procedure is being performed."<ref name="unicef2">[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 23.</ref>}}<ref>For Australia, New Zealand, Europe, Scandinavia, the United States and Canada, [http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf UNICEF 2005] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf |date=20180928122738 }}, p. 4.</ref>。

