實現女陰殘割的人認為女陰殘割主要是表示性別的差異，依此觀點，女陰殘割是對女性的去男性化，而男性的割禮是對男性的去女性化<ref>Rogaia Mustafa Abusharaf, "Introduction: The Custom in Question," in Abusharaf 2007, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA8 8] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA8 |date=20170908222903 }}; El Guindi 2007, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=8VQxt634pfcC&pg=PA36 36–37].</ref>。{{le|Fuambai Ahmadu|Fuambai Ahmadu}}是[[塞拉利昂|獅子山]]{{le|科诺族|Kono people}}的人類學家，在進入{{le|桑德社群|Sande society}}時接受了[[阴蒂切除术|阴蒂切除术]]，作為成人的象徵。她認為強調陰蒂在女性性機能中重要性的想法是男性中心的假設，非洲的女性符號是子宮的受孕<ref>[[Fuambai_Ahmadu|Fuambai Ahmadu]], "Rites and Wrongs: An Insider/Outsider Reflects on Power and Excision," in Shell-Duncan and Hernlund 2000, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=rhhRXiJIGEcC&pg=PA284 284–285].</ref>，鎖陰手術強調封閉及受孕的概念。加拿大人類學家Janice Boddy提到：「阴蒂切除完成了孩童性器官的社會定義，去除了外在輪廓上的雌雄同体。因此女性的身體是被包覆的、封閉的，有生育能力的血液封閉在其中，而男性的身體是不隱藏的、開放的，暴露的。」<ref>Janice Boddy, ''Civilizing Women: British Crusades in Colonial Sudan'', Princeton: Princeton University Press, 2007, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA112 112]. Also see [http://www.jstor.org/stable/25064860 Silverman 2004] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/25064860 |date=20201102154225 }}, p. 429.</ref>

在習慣進行鎖陰手術的族群中，一般會希望女性的生殖器是光滑、乾燥、無氣味的，不論男性或女性都會排斥自然正常的外陰<ref>Ellen Gruenbaum, [http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 "Socio-Cultural Dynamics of Female Genital Cutting: Research Findings, Gaps, and Directions"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 |date=20201103171324 }}, ''Culture, Health & Sexuality'', 7(5), September–October 2005 (pp. 429–441), pp. 435–436.</ref>。男性似乎會享受用陰莖將鎖陰部位頂開的成果<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 Gruenbaum 2005] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 |date=20201103171324 }}, p. 437; Gruenbaum 2001, p. 140; [[Janice_Boddy|Janice Boddy]], ''Wombs and Alien Spirits: Women, Men, and the Zar Cult in Northern Sudan'', Madison: University of Wisconsin Press, 1989, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=TK6NIp5uVwsC&pg=PA52 52] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=TK6NIp5uVwsC&pg=PA52 |date=20130921060824 }}.</ref>。由於進行過鎖陰手術的外陰較光滑，這些族群也認為鎖陰手術有助於清潔衛生<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 Gruenbaum 2005] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 |date=20201103171324 }}, p. 437.</ref>。女性會為了[[乾陰道性交|減少陰道潤滑]]而在陰道中塞入樹葉、树皮、牙膏<!--and Vicks menthol rub-->等物品。世界衛生組織將這類的行為歸類在第4型女陰殘割中，因為這些在性交中增加的摩擦會造成破皮，也會提高感染的風險<ref>Bagnol and Mariano 2011, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=xSqIrrswbG0C&pg=PA277 277–281]; for Type IV, [http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, pp. 27–28.</ref>。

在問卷中女性支持女陰殘割的常見理由包括社會認同、宗教、清潔衛生、保持貞節、適於結婚及增加男性的性快感<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 67.</ref>。在一份1983年發表，針對北蘇丹的研究中指出，3210名女性中只有558人（17.4%）反對女陰殘割，贊成的人贊成陰唇切除及鎖陰手術過於陰蒂切除術<ref>Asma El Dareer, [http://ije.oxfordjournals.org/content/12/2/138.abstract "Attitudes of Sudanese People to the Practice of Female Circumcision"] {{Wayback|url=http://ije.oxfordjournals.org/content/12/2/138.abstract |date=20151101151017 }}, ''International Journal of Epidemiology'', 12(2), 1983 (pp. 138–144), p. 140. {{PMID|6874206}} {{doi|10.1093/ije/12.2.138}}</ref>。不過女性的態度也在慢慢改變。2000年時蘇丹有42%知道女陰殘割的女性認為此作法需繼續實施<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 178.</ref>。在2006年時，在馬里、幾內亞、獅子山、索馬利亞、岡比亞及埃及有超過50%的女性認為應該繼續女陰殘割，而在非洲其他地區、伊拉克及葉門的大部份女性認為不應該再進行女陰殘割，不過在一些國家中，贊成和反對的比例其實差距不大<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 52: "The highest levels of support can be found in Mali, Guinea, Sierra Leone, Somalia, Gambia and Egypt, where more than half the female population think the practice should continue." Also see Figure 6.1, p. 54 and Figures 8.1A – 8.1D, pp. 90–91.</ref>。

===社會規定===
[[File:Molly_Melching,_Tostan,_2007.jpg|thumb]]

針對那些願意為其女兒進行女陰殘割的女性，联合国儿童基金会認為這是：「自我執行的社會習俗」，這些家庭認為需要遵守，以避免沒進行女陰殘割的女兒遭到社會的排斥<ref name=UNICEF20123p15>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 15.</ref>。

美國人類學家Ellen Gruenbaum在1970年代研究指出，阿拉伯人中已接受女性殘割的女孩會嘲笑哪些沒有接受女性殘割的{{le|哲爾馬人|Zabarma people|哲爾馬}}女孩：「嘿！髒鬼！」（''Ya, Ghalfa!''），哲爾馬女孩會反諷他們「mutmura」（mutmura是一種穀倉，常需要打開及關閉，就像接受鎖陰手術的女性一樣）。不過她們仍會感受到壓力，回去會問母親說：「怎麼回事！我們沒有像阿拉伯人一樣的小刀（可以進行鎖陰手術）嗎？」<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 Gruenbaum 2005] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/4005473 |date=20201103171324 }}, pp. 432–433.</ref>

由於相關的醫學資訊的不足，也因為施行女陰殘割者會對女陰殘割的後果加以淡化，因此，女性不會將其身體健康的情形和女陰殘割聯想到一起。拉拉·白爾德（Lala Baldé）是塞內加爾梅迪納·謝里夫村（Medina Cherif）的女性組織領袖，她在1998年告訴Mackie說，當女孩們生病甚至死亡時，會歸因於邪靈的影響。當其他女性知道女陰殘割和健康惡化之間的因果關係時，她們崩溃痛哭。他認為在提供這些資訊前後的調查，可以看出對女陰殘割的支持程度有非常明顯的變化<ref>[http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/FGCHarmlessPractice.pdf Mackie 2003] {{Wayback|url=http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/FGCHarmlessPractice.pdf |date=20170808210842 }}, pp. 147–148.</ref>。

1991年由Molly Melching成立的美國非營利組織{{le|Tosta|Tostan}}在許多國家提出了社區赋权方案，著重在識字、衛生相關教育及地區的民主，讓女性可以做自己的決定<ref>[https://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/publications/2013/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf UNICEF-UNFPA 2012] {{Wayback|url=https://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/publications/2013/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf |date=20140611084959 }}, pp. 21–22.<p>
Nafissatou J. Diop, Amadou Moreau, Hélène Benga, [http://www.unicef.org/wcaro/wcaro_SEN_TOSTAN_EarlyMarriage.pdf "Evaluation of the Long-term Impact of the TOSTAN Programme on the Abandonment of FGM/C and Early Marriage: Results from a qualitative study in Senega"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/wcaro/wcaro_SEN_TOSTAN_EarlyMarriage.pdf |date=20190503104707 }}, UNICEF, January 2008.<p>
Louisa Kasdon, [http://www.louisakasdon.com/userFiles/file/32_pdfver.pdf "A Tradition No Longer"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.louisakasdon.com/userFiles/file/32_pdfver.pdf |date=20160303203251 }}, ''World & I'', November–December 2005, pp. 66–73.<p>
Jean Faraca, [http://wpr.net/webcasting/audioarchives_display.cfm?Code=hoe&StartRow=173&Repeats=no "Confronting Female Genital Cutting"], Wisconsin Public Radio, interview with [[Molly_Melching|Molly Melching]] and [[Gerry_Mackie|Gerry Mackie]], 3 November 2011, from 2:43 mins.</ref>。1997年Malicounda Bambara配合Tostan方案，成為第一個廢止女陰殘割的村莊，在2014年在八個國家已有超過七千個社群放弃女陰殘割和[[童婚|童婚]]<ref>For Malicounda Bambara, [https://web.archive.org/web/20131029210333/http://www.polisci.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/BeginningOfEndMackie2000.pdf Mackie 2000], p. 256ff; for over 7,000 communities, [http://www.tostan.org/community-empowerment-program "Our Success"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.tostan.org/community-empowerment-program |date=20170315032617 }}, Tostan, accessed 25 October 2014.</ref>。有一個聯合國人口基金會和联合国儿童基金会的聯合計劃2014年為止已在非洲十五個國家進行，也是依相同的方式進行<ref name=UNICEF20123p15/>。

===宗教===
<!--{{further|Religious views on female genital mutilation}}-->
[[File:Keur_Simbara,_Senegal_(8592417042).jpg|thumb]]

問卷發現非洲有許多人認為女陰殘割是宗教上的要求，特別是在馬里，茅利塔利亞，幾內亞及埃及等國家，有此想法的人特別的多<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 69–70; Figure 6.12, p. 71.</ref>。格林鲍姆（Gruenbaum）提到當地的人不太會區分此實務是出於宗教、習俗還是貞操，因此不太容易說明這數據進一步的意義<ref>Gruenbaum 2001, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=JOXmOLBd4E4C&pg=PA50 50]; [https://web.archive.org/web/20131014151512/http://www.polisci.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/UNICEF.pdf Mackie and LeJeune 2008], p. 8.</ref>在一個[[联合国人口基金|联合国人口基金]]及[[聯合國兒童基金會|聯合國兒童基金會]]合作的計劃案中，在2008年到2013年間，有20941位宗教領袖及傳統領袖公開說明女陰殘割和宗教無關，宗教領袖發出了2898篇宗教敕令，反對女陰殘割<ref name=jointprogrammeevaluationp26>[https://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/publications/2014/Joint%20Programme%20on%20FGMC%20Summary%20Report.pdf ''UNFPA-UNICEF Joint Programme on Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting: Accelerating Change]{{dead link|date=February 2016}}, Summary Report of Phase I, 2008–2013'' (hereafter 2013 UNFPA-UNICEF Joint Programme evaluation), p. 26.</ref>。

雖然女陰殘割最早出現在東北非的時間是在伊斯蘭教之前，不過因為伊斯蘭教強調女性的貞操及隔離，因此此一實務開始認為和伊斯蘭教有關{{efn|Gerry Mackie, 1996: "FGM is pre-Islamic but was exaggerated by its intersection with the Islamic modesty code of family honor, female purity, virginity, chastity, fidelity, and seclusion."<ref>[http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf Mackie 1996] {{Wayback|url=http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf |date=20170807142229 }}, p. 1008.</ref>}}。在[[可蘭經|可蘭經]]中沒有提到女陰殘割，在數篇[[聖訓|聖訓]]（一般認為是記錄[[穆罕默德|穆罕默德]]的言行錄）中讚賞這種行為，認為是高貴的，但不是必須的，其中也有建議使用較溫和的方式，對婦女比較仁慈{{efn|[[Gerry_Mackie|Gerry Mackie]], 1996: "The Koran is silent on FGM, but several ''hadith'' (sayings attributed to Mohammed) recommend attenuating the practice for the woman's sake, praise it as noble but not commanded, or advise that female converts refrain from mutilation because even if pleasing to the husband it is painful to the wife."<ref>[http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf Mackie 1996] {{Wayback|url=http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf |date=20170807142229 }}, pp. 1004–1005.</ref>}}<ref>Also see Ibrahim Lethome Asmani, Maryam Sheikh Abdi, [http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/De-linking%20FGM%20from%20Islam%20final%20report.pdf "De-linking Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting from Islam"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/De-linking%20FGM%20from%20Islam%20final%20report.pdf |date=20170221230457 }}, USAID/UNFPA, 2008.</ref>。2007年在開羅舉行的艾資哈爾大學伊斯蘭研究最高委員會中認定：「女陰殘割在核心伊斯蘭教法及其他部分規定中都沒有依據。」<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/egypt/media_3875.html "Fresh progress toward the elimination of female genital mutilation and cutting in Egypt"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/egypt/media_3875.html |date=20100831044048 }}, UNICEF, 2 July 2007; [http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 70.</ref>{{efn|Maggie Michael, Associated Press, 2007: "[Egypt's] supreme religious authorities stressed that Islam is against female circumcision. It's prohibited, prohibited, prohibited," Grand Mufti Ali Gomaa said on the privately owned al-Mahwar network."<ref>Maggie Michael, [http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/06/29/AR2007062901284.html "Egypt Officials Ban Female Circumcision"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/06/29/AR2007062901284.html |date=20170920162546 }}, Associated Press, 29 June 2007, p. 2.</ref>}}
也有[[泛靈論|泛靈論]]的族群進行女陰殘割，特別是在幾內亞及馬里。也有基督徒進行女陰殘割的情形<ref>For animist groups, [http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 175; for Christians, p. 73.</ref>，例如在尼日，約有55%的基督徒婦女及女孩進行了女陰殘割，而穆斯林族群中只有2%<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, front page: "Niger. 55% of Christian girls and women have undergone FGM/C, compared to 2% of Muslim girls and women," and p. 73.</ref>。[[聖經|聖經]]上只提到男性的割禮，沒提到女陰殘割，而到非洲的宣教士是最早反對女陰殘割的一群人之一<ref>Samuel Waje Kunhiyop, ''African Christian Ethics'', Zondervan, 2008, p. 297: "Nowhere in all of Scripture or in any of recorded church history is there even a hint that women were to be circumcised."<p>
For missionaries, Jocelyn Murray, [http://www.jstor.org/stable/1594780 "The Church Missionary Society and the 'Female Circumcision' Issue in Kenya 1929–1932"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/1594780 |date=20170101060007 }}, ''Journal of Religion in Africa'', 8(2), 1976, pp. 92–104.</ref>。非洲的猶太教族群中只有衣索比亞的[[贝塔以色列|貝塔以色列人]]有進行女性器切除。猶太教要求男性實行割禮，反對女陰殘割<ref>Shaye J. D. Cohen, ''Why Aren't Jewish Women Circumcised? Gender and Covenant In Judaism'', Berkeley: University of California Press, 2005, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=PmL-LogqJ-YC&pg=PA59 59] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=PmL-LogqJ-YC&pg=PA59 |date=20131009083441 }}; [[Adele_Berlin|Adele Berlin]] (ed.), "Circumcision," ''The Oxford Dictionary of the Jewish Religion'', New York: Oxford University Press, 2011, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=hKAaJXvUaUoC&pg=PA173 173].</ref>。
