希臘地理學家[[斯特拉波|斯特拉波]]（西元前64年至西元23年）在西元前25年造訪埃及後，寫下了有關女陰殘割的描述（如右）{{efn|[[Strabo|Strabo]], ''[[Geographica|Geographica]]'', c. 25 BCE: "One of the customs most zealously observed among the Aegyptians is this, that they rear every child that is born, and circumcise [περιτέμνειν, ''peritemnein''] the males, and excise [''ektemnein''] the females, as is also customary among the Jews, who are also Aegyptians in origin, as I have already stated in my account of them."<ref>[[Strabo|Strabo]], ''[[Geographica|Geographica]]'', [http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/17B*.html#ref273 Book VII, chapter 2], 17.2.5. Cohen 2005, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=PmL-LogqJ-YC&pg=PA59 59ff] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=PmL-LogqJ-YC&pg=PA59 |date=20131009083441 }}, argues that Strabo conflated the Jews with the Egyptians).</ref>{{pb}}
[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/16D*.html Book XVI, chapter 4], 16.4.9: "And then to the Harbour of Antiphilus, and, above this, to the Creophagi [meat-eaters], of whom the males have their sexual glands mutilated [''kolobos''] and the women are excised [''ektemnein''] in the Jewish fashion."}}{{efn|Knight 2001 writes that there is one extant reference from antiquity, from [[Xanthus_(historian)|Xanthus of Lydia]] in the fifth century BCE, that may allude to FGM outside Egypt. Xanthus wrote, in a history of [[呂底亞|Lydia]]: "The Lydians arrived at such a state of delicacy that they were even the first to 'castrate' their women." Knight argues that the "castration", which is not described, may have kept women youthful, in the sense of allowing the Lydian king to have intercourse with them without pregnancy. Knight concludes that it may have been a reference to sterilization, not FGM.<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 Knight 2001] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 |date=20190502192047 }}, p. 326.</ref>}}。哲學家[[斐洛|斐洛]]（西元前20年至西元50年）也寫道：「埃及人依照其國家的習俗，會在十四歲的少年及少女舉行割禮，那時少年已開始有精子，少女也開始有月經。」<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 Knight 2001] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 |date=20190502192047 }}, p. 333.</ref>有一份認為是希臘醫師[[盖伦|盖伦]]寫的文章中也有提到：「當年輕女性的陰蒂大幅度伸出時，埃及人會認為應該將其切除。」<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 Knight 2001] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 |date=20190502192047 }}, p. 326 (Knight writes that the attribution to Galen is suspect).</ref>

另一位希臘醫生{{le|阿弥陀的埃提乌斯|Aëtius of Amida}}（第 5世紀中至第6 世紀中）在其"Sixteen Books on Medicine"中的第16本中，引用了醫生Philomenes的話。當陰蒂長的太大，或是當和衣服磨擦時會引發性衝動時，就會進行女陰殘割。埃提乌斯說：「這種情形下，埃及人似乎認為在陰蒂大幅變大之前切除會比較妥當，尤其是少女快要嫁人的時候。」

<blockquote style="background:none; margin-right:5em; margin-left:0; border-left:solid 5px #ccc; padding:1.5em;">
手術是以這樣的方式進行：少女坐在椅子上，一個充滿肌肉的少年站在她後面，手臂在少女的大腿下面，讓少女的腿分開，並且穩住身體及腿。醫生站在少女前面，用左手的泛口钳夾住少女的陰蒂，並且往外拉，右手從钳夾住的點割下陰蒂。

陰蒂不會完全切除，會保留部份的組織，長度大約會和鼻孔相當。手術只是為了切除過多的組織。因為陰蒂是類似皮膚的組織，若割除太多，怕會出現尿瘘的情形<ref name=Knight2001p327>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 Knight 2001] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 |date=20190502192047 }}, pp. 327–328 (a paragraph break has been added for ease of reading).</ref></blockquote>

接下來會用海綿、[[乳香|乳香]]粉、酒或冰水清理外陰道，然後用浸滿醋的亞麻繃帶包紮至第七天，接著使用[[爐甘石洗劑|爐甘石洗劑]]、玫瑰花瓣、棗核或是「烤過黏土製成的陰部塗抹粉末」<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 Knight 2001] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/3080631 |date=20190502192047 }}, p. 328.</ref>。

鎖陰手術的起源不明，但後來演變成和奴隸有關。Mackie曾引述葡萄牙宣教士 {{le|João dos Santos|João dos Santos}}在1609年提到[[摩加迪休|摩加迪休]]群島上人們的文字：“他們的習俗㑹將女性（的陰部）縫合，特別是年輕的女奴，使她們無法生育，也讓女奴 比較好賣，一方面是貞節，也有助於主人對她們的信任。”英國的探險家{{le|威廉·乔治·布朗|William George Browne}}在1799年也寫到埃及人會進行女陰殘割，而且會為女奴進行鎖陰手術以避免懷孕<ref>[http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf Mackie 1996] {{Wayback|url=http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf |date=20170807142229 }}, p. 1003.</ref>。Mackie認為是：「一項和女奴有關的手術變成了榮譽的象徵。」<ref>[http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf Mackie 1996] {{Wayback|url=http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/MackieASR.pdf |date=20170807142229 }}, p. 1009.</ref>

===歐洲及美國===
[[File:Isaac_Baker_Brown.jpg|thumb]]

19世紀歐洲及美國的婦產科醫生用切除陰蒂的方式來治療精神錯亂及女性的自慰<ref>Sarah W. Rodriguez, [http://jhmas.oxfordjournals.org/content/63/3/323 "Rethinking the History of Female Circumcision and Clitoridectomy: American Medicine and Female Sexuality in the Late Nineteenth Century"] {{Wayback|url=http://jhmas.oxfordjournals.org/content/63/3/323 |date=20170101055239 }}, ''Journal of the History of Medicine and Allied Sciences''. 63(3), July 2008, pp. 323–347. {{PMID|18065832}} {{doi|10.1093/jhmas/jrm044}}</ref>。英國醫生罗伯特·托马斯在1813年建議用切除陰蒂來治療色情狂<ref>Robert Thomas, ''The Modern Practice of Physick'', London: Longman, Hurst, Rees, Orme, and Brown, 1813, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=yK9YAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA585 585–586].<p>
Edward Shorter, ''From Paralysis to Fatigue: A History of Psychosomatic Illness in the Modern Era'', New York: Simon and Schuster, 2008, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=I87S-xL6Q1wC&pg=PA82 82] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=I87S-xL6Q1wC&pg=PA82 |date=20140705103700 }}.</ref>。第一個有記錄的西方[[陰蒂切除術|切除陰蒂]]是記載在1825年的《[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|柳葉刀]]》雜誌上，是1822年在柏林由{{le|卡尔·费迪南德·冯·格雷夫|Karl Ferdinand von Graefe}}進行，是對一位十五歲，自慰過度的女性所施行的手術<ref>Shorter 2008, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=I87S-xL6Q1wC&pg=PA82 82] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=I87S-xL6Q1wC&pg=PA82 |date=20140705103700 }}; Uriel Elchalal, et al., [http://journals.lww.com/obgynsurvey/Abstract/1997/10000/Ritualistic_Female_Genital_Mutilation__Current.22.aspx "Ritualistic Female Genital Mutilation: Current Status and Future Outlook"] {{Wayback|url=http://journals.lww.com/obgynsurvey/Abstract/1997/10000/Ritualistic_Female_Genital_Mutilation__Current.22.aspx |date=20141028074433 }}, ''Obstetrical & Gynecological Survey'', 52(10), October 1997, pp. 643–651. {{PMID|9326757}}</ref>。

{{le|艾萨克·贝克·布朗|Isaac Baker Brown}}是英國的婦產科醫生，{{le|伦敦医学会|Medical Society of London}}的主席，也是1845年倫敦[[倫敦聖瑪麗醫院|聖瑪麗醫院]]的共同創辦人，他相信自慰，或是「對於陰蒂的不正常刺激」會造成耻骨神经末梢的兴奋，會造成[[歇斯底里|歇斯底里]]、脊髓刺激、痙攣、白痴、癫狂甚至死亡」<ref>[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9326757 Elchalal, et al, 1997] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9326757 |date=20131105011843 }}; Peter Lewis Allen, ''The Wages of Sin: Sex and Disease, Past and Present'', Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 2000, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=SpQOUx5zoBEC&pg=PA106 106] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SpQOUx5zoBEC&pg=PA106 |date=20140102072854 }}.</ref>。依照在1873年《医疗时报公报》中訃聞中提到內容，「只要他有機會，就會動手切除陰蒂。」<ref>J. F. C. 1873, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=gZ4EAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA155 155]; Allen 2000, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=SpQOUx5zoBEC&pg=PA106 106] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SpQOUx5zoBEC&pg=PA106 |date=20140102072854 }}.</ref>布朗醫生在1859年到1866之間進行了多次的陰蒂切除手術。他後來發表了《对女性某些形式的精神错乱，癫痫，僵住症，和歇斯底里的可治癒性》（1866年），倫敦的醫師指責他是騙子，並將他趕出{{le|倫敦產科協會|Obstetrical Society of London}}<ref>John Black, [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1296388/pdf/jrsocmed00038-0048.pdf "Female genital mutilation: a contemporary issue, and a Victorian obsession"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1296388/pdf/jrsocmed00038-0048.pdf |date=20211223001942 }}, ''Journal of the Royal Society of Medicine'', 90, July 1997 (pp. 402–405), p. 403, 404–405. {{PMID|9290425}} {{PMC|1296388}}<p>
Allen 2000, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=SpQOUx5zoBEC&pg=PA106 106] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SpQOUx5zoBEC&pg=PA106 |date=20140102072854 }}; also see Elizabeth Sheehan, [http://www.jstor.org/stable/647794?seq=2 "Victorian Clitoridectomy: Isaac Baker Brown and His Harmless Operative Procedure"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/647794?seq=2 |date=20190503042141 }}, ''Medical Anthropology Newsletter'', 12(4), August 1981. {{PMID|12263443}}</ref>。

美國的[[J.·馬里恩·西姆斯|J.·馬里恩·西姆斯]]延續了布朗醫師的研究，在1862年在一名女性病患主訴經痛、抽搐和膀胱问题後，切開其子宮頸，並且切除陰蒂，「用布朗醫師建議的方式來緩解緊張及歇斯底里的状态。」<ref>Deborah Kuhn McGregor, ''From Midwives to Medicine: The Birth of American Gynecology'', New Brunswick: Rutgers University Press, 1998, p. 146.</ref>。在同一世紀，紐奧蘭的外科醫生A. J. Bloch因一名二歲的女童持續性的自慰，切除其陰蒂<ref>John Milton Hoberman, ''Testosterone Dreams: Rejuvenation, Aphrodisia, Doping'', University of California Press, 2005, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=bT_2oWnOaXgC&pg=PA63 63].</ref>。依照1985年产科和妇科调查的論文，1960年代美國還有用切除陰蒂來治療歇斯底里，色情狂和[[女同性恋|女同性恋]]<ref>Lawrence Cutner, [http://journals.lww.com/obgynsurvey/Citation/1985/07000/Female_Genital_Mutilation_.4.aspx "Female genital mutilation"] {{Wayback|url=http://journals.lww.com/obgynsurvey/Citation/1985/07000/Female_Genital_Mutilation_.4.aspx |date=20141028073249 }}, ''Obstetrical & Gynecological Survey'', 40(7), July 1985, pp. 437–443. {{PMID|4022475}} Cited in Nawal M. Nour, [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2582648/ "Female Genital Cutting: A Persisting Practice"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2582648/ |date=20210112200005 }}, ''Reviews in Obstetrics and Gynecology'', 1(3), Summer 2008, pp. 135–139. {{PMID|19015765}} {{PMC|2582648}}<p>Also see G. J. Barker-Benfield, ''The Horrors of the Half-Known Life: Male Attitudes Toward Women and Sexuality in Nineteenth-Century America'', New York: Routledge, 1999, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=0QKUAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA113 113].</ref>。
