二十世紀初，{{le|约翰·阿瑟|John Arthur}}加入在[[英屬東非|英屬東非]]（現今[[肯亞|肯亞]]）基庫尤的蘇格蘭福音會（CSM）服事，新教传教士當時就開始反對女性割禮的活動。[[基庫尤人|基庫尤人]]是肯亞的主要族群，他們稱男生及女生的割禮為irua，男性是割除包皮，女性則是類型二的女陰殘割（部分或全部切除小陰唇），這是基庫尤人重要的族群記號，沒有實行割禮的女性稱為irugu，會被逐出社群之外<ref>Lynn M. Thomas,{{" '}}Ngaitana (I will circumcise myself)': Lessons from Colonial Campaigns to Ban Excision in Meru, Kenya" in Shell-Duncan and Hernlund, 2000, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=rhhRXiJIGEcC&pg=PA132 132] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=rhhRXiJIGEcC&pg=PA132 |date=20130921061049 }}.<p>
For ''irua'', Jomo Kenyatta, ''Facing Mount Kenya'', New York: Vintage Books, 1962 [1938], p. 129; for ''irugu'' being outcasts, Kenyatta, p. 127, and Zabus 2008, pp. 48–49.</ref>

[[喬莫·肯雅塔|喬莫·肯雅塔]]是{{le|基庫尤中央聯盟|Kikuyu Central Association}}的主席及1963年起的首任肯亞總理，他在1938年提到，對於基庫尤人而言，女性割禮的規定：「是整個部落法律、宗教及道德中，不可缺少的条件」（conditio sine qua non）。沒有一個正常的基庫尤人會和沒有行割禮的人發生性關係或結婚。女性對部落的責任從她的成年禮開始。她在部落歷史中的記錄會從這一天開始，部落會依當時的事件為受割禮的女性命名，這是基庫尤的[[口头传统|口头传统]]，讓基庫尤人可以追溯上百年前的人物及事件<ref>Kenyatta 1962 [1938], pp. 127–130.</ref>。

[[File:Hulda_Stumpf,_Africa_Inland_Mission_conference.jpg|thumb]]

1925年起，蘇格蘭福音會開始宣佈非洲的基督徒禁止進行女陰殘割，許多非洲的宣教機構也有類似的聲明。蘇格蘭福音會宣佈進行女陰殘割的非洲人會被逐出教會，因此有上百人離開教會或是被趕出教會<ref>Klaus Fiedler, ''Christianity and African Culture'', Leiden: Brill, 1996, p. 75.</ref>。這樣的對峙使得女陰殘割成為肯亞獨立運動的焦點，肯亞在1929年至1931年有 {{le|1929年至1932年肯亞反對女陰殘割運動|Campaign against female genital mutilation in Kenya in 1929–32}}<ref>Boddy 2007, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA241 241–245] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA241 |date=20131013205006 }}.<p>
Also see Ronald Hyam, ''Empire and Sexuality: The British Experience'', Manchester: Manchester University Press, 1990; [http://www.jstor.org/stable/1594780 Murray 1976] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/1594780 |date=20170101060007 }}, pp. 92–104.</ref>，殖民政府及教會反對女陰殘割，而基庫尤人反對殖民政府及教會的作法。

1929年肯亞宣教協會開始認為女陰殘割不是割禮，而是「對女性的性残害」，而個人是否進行女陰殘割也就代表他忠於基督教會或是忠於{{le|基庫尤中央聯盟|Kikuyu Central Association}}<ref>Thomas 2000, p. 132; for the "sexual mutilation of women", Karanja 2009, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=F1ezIgyomGIC&pg=PA93 93] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=F1ezIgyomGIC&pg=PA93 |date=20170908222703 }}, n. 631.<p>
Also see Robert Strayer, Jocelyn Murray, "The CMS and Female Circumcision", in Robert Strayer (ed.), ''The Making of Missionary Communities in East Africa'', New York: State University of New York Press, 1978, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=9kpLvKnZCR8C&pg=PA139 139ff].</ref>。{{le|霍爾達·史敦夫|Hulda Stumpf}}是{{le|非洲內地會|Africa Inland Mission}}的美國宣教士，在她協助成立的女子學校中反對女陰殘割，在1930年被謀殺。肯亞總督[[爱德华·格里格|爱德华·格里格]]告訴肯亞[[殖民地部|殖民地辦公室]]說，兇手試圖要為史敦夫進行女陰殘割<ref>Boddy 2007, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA241 241] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA241 |date=20131013205006 }}, [http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA241 244] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=T77ui7IPNwkC&pg=PA241 |date=20131013205006 }}.<p>
Dana Lee Robert, ''American Women in Mission: A Social History of Their Thought and Practice'', Macon: Mercer University Press, 1996, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=98eI044RjlwC&pg=PA230 230].</ref>。

1956年時[[梅魯族|梅魯族]]長老協會（Njuri Nchecke）宣佈禁止女陰殘割。然而此舉卻引起族人反抗，之後的三年內，數千名少女用小刀為彼此進行女陰殘割。這個活動在梅魯族稱為「Ngaitana」（自行割禮），如此命名是因為雖然手術是由女孩的朋友所執行，但為了避免提及操刀者的名字，女孩會說是他們自己動刀的。歷史學家萊恩·湯瑪斯（Lynn Thomas）將這個視為是女陰殘割歷史中的重要內容，因為清楚的看出女陰殘割的受害者也成為了加害者<ref>Thomas 2000, pp. [http://books.google.com/books?id=rhhRXiJIGEcC&pg=PA129 129–131] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=rhhRXiJIGEcC&pg=PA129 |date=20130921054614 }} (p. 131 for the girls as "central actors"); Lynn Thomas, ''Politics of the Womb: Women, Reproduction, and the State in Kenya'', Berkeley: University of California Press, 2003, pp. 89–91.<p>
Also see Lynn M. Thomas, [http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1468-0424.1996.tb00062.x/abstract Ngaitana (I will circumcise myself)': The Gender and Generational Politics of the 1956 Ban on Clitoridectomy in Meru, Kenya"] {{Wayback|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1468-0424.1996.tb00062.x/abstract |date=20160510204425 }}, ''Gender and History'', 8(3), November 1996, pp. 338–363.<p>
Kenya banned FGM in 2011; see [http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf UNFPA–UNICEF 2012] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf |date=20180316152947 }}, p. 14.</ref>

===反對聲浪持續擴大===
[[File:Nawal_el_Saadawi_01.JPG|thumb]]是一位批評女陰殘割的非洲女權主義者。]]

1920年代在埃及展開反對女陰殘割的活動，這是目前已知第一場不是由殖民政府或是傳教士發起的反對女陰殘割活動。當時埃及醫師社群號召禁止女陰殘割<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 10, calls the Egyptian Doctors' Society opposition the "first known campaign" against FGM; for independence, Boddy 2007, p. 147.</ref>，同時蘇丹的宗教領袖及英籍婦女也響應活動。蘇丹在1946年禁止鎖陰術，但這條法律執行成效向來不彰<ref>Boddy 2007, pp. 202, 299.</ref>{{efn|FGM is still practised in Sudan. Some states banned it in 2008–2009, but {{as of|2013|lc=y}}, there was no national legislation.<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 2, 9.</ref>}}。埃及政府在1959年在州營醫院禁止鎖陰術，但卻允許在雙親要求下執行部分陰蒂切除術<ref>Elizabeth Heger Boyle, ''Female Genital Cutting: Cultural Conflict in the Global Community'', Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press, 2002, pp. 92, 103.</ref>{{efn|Egypt banned FGM entirely in 2007.}}

聯合國在1959年要求世界衛生組織調查女陰殘割，但世界衛生組織回應這不是醫療相關議題<ref>Boyle 2002, p. 41.</ref>。女性主義者在1970年代開始提出此一議題<ref>Bagnol and Mariano 2011, p. 281.</ref>。埃及女醫生[[納瓦勒·薩達|納瓦勒·薩達]]在1972年出版的《女人與性》（Women and Sex）中批評女陰殘割，這本書在埃及是禁書，她也因為失去了公共衛生總幹事的工作<ref name=Khaleeli2010>Gruenbaum 2001, p. 22.<p>
Homa Khaleeli, [http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2010/apr/15/nawal-el-saadawi-egyptian-feminist "Nawal El Saadawi: Egypt's radical feminist"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2010/apr/15/nawal-el-saadawi-egyptian-feminist |date=20150926003949 }}, ''The Guardian'', 15 April 2010.<p>
Jenna Krajeski, [http://www.newyorker.com/books/page-turner/the-books-of-nawal-el-saadawi "The Books of Nawal El Saadawi"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newyorker.com/books/page-turner/the-books-of-nawal-el-saadawi |date=20210123060841 }}, ''The New Yorker'', 7 March 2011.<p>
Jenna Krajeski, [http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2011/03/14/rebellion-2 "Rebellion"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2011/03/14/rebellion-2 |date=20171031203444 }}, ''The New Yorker'', 14 March 2011.</ref>。她在1980年出版的《夏娃隱藏的臉：阿拉伯世界的女性》（''The Hidden Face of Eve: Women in the Arab World''）中〈女孩的割禮〉一節中描述她自己在六歲時接受陰蒂切除術的情形：

<blockquote style="background:none; margin-right:5em; margin-left:0; border-left:solid 5px #ccc; padding:1.5em;">
我不知道他們從我身上切除了什麼，我沒有去找。我只是哭，向我的媽媽呼喚求助。但最令人驚嚇的是我環顧四周，發現她就站在我身邊，是的，就是她，我沒有弄錯，身為我的媽媽，站在這一群陌生人之間，和他們微笑及說話，就好像他們幾分鐘前沒有參與殺害她女兒的行動一樣<ref>Nawal El Saadawi, ''The Hidden Face of Eve'', London: Zed Books, 2007 [1980], p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=u5n9zUZuVI8C&pg=PA14 14].</ref>。</blockquote>

1975年時，美國社會科學家羅斯·歐德菲爾德·海耶斯（Rose Oldfield Hayes）發表女陰殘割相關記錄，她是第一位發表這類記錄的女性學者，她是在和蘇丹的女性直接討論此議題後，得到有關資料。她在《美國民族學家》期刊發表的論文中，稱這種習俗為「女陰殘割」（female genital mutilation），帶來學術界更廣泛的注意<ref>[http://www.jstor.org/stable/643328 Hayes 1975] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/643328 |date=20201115002444 }}, p. 618; Gruenbaum 2001, p. 21.</ref>。

四年之後的1979年，奧地利裔美籍的女性主義者{{le|弗蘭·霍斯肯|Fran Hosken}}出版了《霍斯肯報告：女性生殖器及性器官殘割》（The Hosken Report: Genital and Sexual Mutilation of Females，1979）。霍斯肯在此本著作中估計，全球約有110,529,000名女性實施過女陰殘割，分布於20個非洲國家<ref>[http://dhsprogram.com/pubs/pdf/WP39/WP39.pdf Yoder and Khan 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://dhsprogram.com/pubs/pdf/WP39/WP39.pdf |date=20171122012927 }}, p. 2.</ref>。這是第一篇提出女陰殘割實施人數的文獻，該數據雖為估計值，但後來進行的幾次調查也大略符合此數字。Mackie認為霍斯肯的著作雖然對於數據與資料來源稍嫌不嚴謹，但喚醒世界對於此議題的重視<ref>[http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/FGCHarmlessPractice.pdf Mackie 2003] {{Wayback|url=http://pages.ucsd.edu/~gmackie/documents/FGCHarmlessPractice.pdf |date=20170808210842 }}, p. 139.</ref>。霍斯肯用「男性暴力的訓練場」來描述女陰殘割，將其中女性的參與者稱為是「參與了毀滅同類的活動」<ref>Hosken 1994 [1979], p. 5.</ref>。這段話造成西方及非洲女性主義者之間的衝突。聯合國在1980年7月於哥本哈根舉行的十年中期會議，非洲女性主義者就杯葛其中一個以霍斯肯為主題的會議<ref>Boyle 2002, p. 47; Bagnol and Mariano 2011, p. 281.</ref>。

在1979年，世界衛生組織在蘇丹[[喀土木|喀土木]]舉辦「傳統習俗影響婦女與孩童健康研討會」，1981年{{le|巴拜克巴德里婦女研究科學協會|Babiker Badri Scientific Association for Women's Studies}}（BBSAWS）也在喀土木舉辦了三天的研習營「攜手對抗女性割禮對女性造成的殘疾與危害」（''Female Circumcision Mutilates and Endangers Women – Combat it!''） 。活動結束後有150位學者與活躍人士簽署，宣示對抗女陰殘割。另一個巴拜克巴德里婦女研究科學協會在1984年舉辦的研習營，其中邀請國際社群，簽署給聯合國的聯合聲明。簽署者同意他們在聯合聲明中所寫到的「女性割禮是對人權的暴力，侵犯女性的[[尊嚴|尊嚴]]，剝奪女性的性慾，並且是對於女性健康的無端羞辱。」<ref>Shahira Ahmed, "Babiker Badri Scientific Association for Women's Studies", in Abusharaf 2007, pp. 176–180.</ref>其中包括了：

<blockquote style="background:none; margin-right:5em; margin-left:0; border-left:solid 5px #ccc; padding:1.5em;">
*建議非洲女性完全根除女性割禮相關手術。
*禁絕所有實務上有關女陰殘割的信仰內涵，如將切除陰蒂視為「聖訓」等等。
*應設計替代儀式，現在一般會稱為「替代式成人禮」<ref>Ahmed 2007, p. 180.</ref></blockquote>

{{le|泛非洲影響婦女及兒童的傳統醫療實務協會|The Inter-African Committee on Traditional Practices Affecting the Health of Women and Children}}1984年成立於[[塞內加爾|塞內加爾]]的[[達喀爾|達喀爾]]，此協會呼籲中止女性割禮這項習俗，1993年在[[維也納|維也納]]舉辦的聯合國[[世界人權會議|世界人權會議]]也提出類似訴求。這次會議將女陰殘割列為[[对妇女的暴力行为|对妇女的暴力行为]]，並認定此議題是違反人權的議題，不只是醫學議題而已<ref>[[Anika_Rahman|Anika Rahman]] and [[Nahid_Toubia|Nahid Toubia]], ''Female Genital Mutilation: A Guide to Laws and Policies Worldwide'', New York: Zed Books, 2000, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=kEG6GaudxQEC&pg=PA110 10–11]; for Vienna, [http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }} p. 8.</ref>。在1990年代到2000年年代，非洲政府嚴懲或是限制女性割禮。在2003年七月，[[非洲聯盟|非洲聯盟]]批准了{{le|馬普拖協議|Maputo Protocol}}中關於女權的部分，支持禁絕女陰殘割<ref>Emma Bonino, [http://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/15/opinion/15iht-edbonino_ed3_.html "A brutal custom: Join forces to banish the mutilation of women"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/15/opinion/15iht-edbonino_ed3_.html |date=20150531165453 }}, ''The New York Times'', 15 September 2004; [https://web.archive.org/web/20110409114818/http://www.africa-union.org/root/au/Documents/Treaties/Text/Protocol%20on%20the%20Rights%20of%20Women.pdf Maputo Protocol], pp. 7–8.</ref>。截至2015年，27個實行女陰殘割的非洲國家中，至少有23個通過禁止法令，不過少數國家仍未完全禁止{{efn|For example, UNICEF 2013 lists Mauritania as having passed legislation against FGM, but (as of that year) it was banned only from being conducted in government facilities or by medical personnel.<ref name="UNICEF2013p8"/>The following countries, in which FGM is concentrated, have placed restrictions on it. An asterisk indicates a ban:

:Benin (2003), Burkina Faso (1996*), Central African Republic (1966, amended 1996), Chad (2003), Côte d'Ivoire (1998), Djibouti (1995, amended 2009*), Egypt (2008*), Eritrea (2007*), Ethiopia (2004*), Ghana (1994, amended 2007), Guinea (1965, amended 2000*), Guinea-Bissau (2011*), Iraq (2011*), Kenya (2001, amended 2011*), Mauritania (2005), Niger (2003), Nigeria (2015*), Senegal (1999*), Somalia (2012*), Sudan, some states (2008–2009), Tanzania (1998), Togo (1998), Uganda (2010*), Yemen (2001*).<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, pp. 8–9;[http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf UNFPA–UNICEF 2012 annual report] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf |date=20180316152947 }}, p. 12].</ref>}}。

===聯合國===
[[File:Mary_Karooro_Okurut_(cropped)_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]

[[聯合國大會|聯合國大會]] 於1993年12月提出的48/104決議案，亦即《[[消除对妇女的暴力行为宣言|消除对妇女的暴力行为宣言]]》，就包含了女陰殘割。聯合國在2003年起，將每年2月6日訂為{{le|女陰殘割國際零容忍日|International Day of Zero Tolerance to Female Genital Mutilation}}<ref>[http://www.un.org/documents/ga/res/48/a48r104.htm "48/104. Declaration on the Elimination of Violence against Women"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.un.org/documents/ga/res/48/a48r104.htm |date=20150220051911 }}, United Nations General Assembly, 20 December 1993.<p>
Charlotte Feldman-Jacobs, [http://www.prb.org/Articles/2009/fgmc.aspx "Commemorating International Day of Zero Tolerance to Female Genital Mutilation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.prb.org/Articles/2009/fgmc.aspx |date=20100213125942 }}, Population Reference Bureau, February 2009.</ref>。同年，[[聯合國兒童基金會|聯合國兒童基金會]]（UNICEF）開始推廣以Gerry Mackie發展的實證性{{le|社會規範方法|social norms approach}}評估介入行為。Gerry 在對於中國如何放棄[[纏足|纏足]]的習俗研究中，利用[[賽局理論|賽局理論]]推估社群究竟如何取得最終共識，而UNICEF也利用此一研究的基礎來進行分析FGM<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 15; Francesca Moneti, David Parker, [http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_insight_eng.pdf ''The Dynamics of Social Change''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_insight_eng.pdf |date=20190503024120 }}, Florence: UNICEF Innocenti Research Centre, October 2010, p. 6.</ref>，並於2005年，在[[佛羅倫斯|佛羅倫斯]]的{{le|因諾琴蒂研究中心|Innocenti Research Centre}}發表該組織的第一份相關研究報告<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 15; Michael Miller and Francesca Moneti, [http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf ''Changing a harmful social convention: Female genital cutting/mutilation''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf |date=20180928122738 }}, Florence: UNICEF Innocenti Research Centre, 2005.</ref>。

2008年，[[聯合國人權事務高級專員辦事處|聯合國人權事務高級專員辦事處]]等多個[[聯合國|聯合國]]組織在內，共同發表了一份聲明，認定女陰殘割是對人權的侵犯<ref>[http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf WHO 2008] {{Wayback|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2008/9789241596442_eng.pdf |date=20130810080948 }}, p. 8; [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 Yoder, Wang and Johansen, 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23720002 |date=20171019061100 }}, p. 190.</ref>。在2012年12月時，聯合國大會通過67/146號決議，要求致力消除女陰殘割<ref name="UN">[http://www.un.org/en/ga/search/view_doc.asp?symbol=A/RES/67/146 "67/146. Intensifying global efforts for the elimination of female genital mutilation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.un.org/en/ga/search/view_doc.asp?symbol=A%2FRES%2F67%2F146 |date=20210129034239 }}, United Nations General Assembly, adopted 20 December 2012.

Emma Bonino, [http://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/20/opinion/global/banning-female-genital-mutilation.html "Banning Female Genital Mutilation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/20/opinion/global/banning-female-genital-mutilation.html |date=20190926064610 }}, ''The New York Times'', 19 December 2012.</ref>。而在2014年7月[[聯合國兒童基金會|聯合國兒童基金會]]和英國政府共同主辦了第一屆女童高峰會（Girl Summit），目標為結束女陰殘割和[[童婚|童婚]]的習俗<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/media/media_74524.html "No time to lose: New UNICEF data show need for urgent action on female genital mutilation and child marriage"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/media_74524.html |date=20141102053603 }}, UNICEF, 22 July 2014; [http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/girl-summit "Girl Summit"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/girl-summit |date=20170909095302 }}, ''The Guardian''.</ref>。

2007年，[[联合国人口基金|联合国人口基金]]（UNFPA） 和 UNICEF 發起一項聯合計畫，旨在使15歲以下少女進行女陰殘割的比例減少四成，並使至少一個國家根絕該習俗。在2008年參與該計畫的國家共15國，包含：[[吉布地|吉布地]]、[[埃及|埃及]]、[[衣索比亞|衣索比亞]]、[[幾內亞|幾內亞]]、[[幾內亞比索|幾內亞比索]]、[[肯亞|肯亞]]、[[塞內加爾|塞內加爾]]，和[[蘇丹|蘇丹]]。隔年，[[布吉內法索|布吉內法索]]、[[甘比亞|甘比亞]]、[[索馬利亞|索馬利亞]]和[[烏干達|烏干達]]加入；2011年，[[马里|马里]]、[[厄利垂亞|厄利垂亞]]、[[茅利塔尼亞|茅利塔尼亞]]也加入該計畫<ref>[https://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/Evaluation_branch/Joint%20Evaluation%20-%20Sept%202013/Main%20Report/FGM-report%2011_15_2013.pdf "UNFPA–UNICEF Joint Programme on Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting: Accelerating Change"]{{dead link|date=February 2016}}, Volume 1, 2008–2012, September 2013, p. viii.</ref>。該計畫的第一階段從2008年到2013年為止，投入了近3700萬美金，當中有2000億的資金是由[[挪威|挪威]]捐獻<ref>[https://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/publications/2014/Joint%20Programme%20on%20FGMC%20Summary%20Report.pdf 2013 UNFPA-UNICEF Joint Programme evaluation]{{dead link|date=February 2016}}, p. 38.</ref>。第二期則由2014年至2017年<ref>[https://www.unfpa.org/files/live/sites/unfpa/files/Documents/FGM/Funding%20Proposal%20for%20Phase%20II%20of%20the%20UNFPA-UNICEF%20Joint%20Programme.PDF "Joint Programme on the Abandonment of Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting. Funding Proposal for a Phase II"]{{dead link|date=February 2016 }}, UNFPA–UNICEF, January 2014.<p>
[http://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/Evaluation_branch/Joint%20Evaluation%20-%20Sept%202013/Management%20Response/FGMC%20Management%20Response%20Joint%20webex%20UNICEF%20Feb%2019%202014.pptx "Joint Programme on the Abandonment of Female Genital Mutilation/Cutting. Management Response and Key Actions"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/Evaluation_branch/Joint%20Evaluation%20-%20Sept%202013/Management%20Response/FGMC%20Management%20Response%20Joint%20webex%20UNICEF%20Feb%2019%202014.pptx |date=20140611065427 }}, UNFPA–UNICEF, 19 February 2014.</ref>。

2013年的計畫中已經讓12,753個社區宣布不進行女陰殘割，整合了5,571個關於女陰殘割的先天與后天的照護預防治療的衛生設施，並且培訓了超過10萬個在照護與預防女陰殘割相關領域的醫生，護士以及助產士。這項計畫幫助了建置烏干達與肯亞的通過儀式替代方案，並在蘇丹支援了早已存在的兒童保護計畫的 Saleema 行動。Saleema 在阿拉伯文的意思是＂完整＂，這個行動促使了這個名詞成為對尚未施行女陰殘割女性的完整表述<ref>[https://www.unfpa.org/webdav/site/global/shared/documents/publications/2014/Joint%20Programme%20on%20FGMC%20Summary%20Report.pdf 2013 UNFPA-UNICEF Joint Programme evaluation]{{dead link|date=February 2016}}, pp. 4, 16–17; for alternative rites of passage and the Saleema initiative, pp. 22–23.</ref>。此計劃也注意到反女陰殘割的執法成效薄弱，即使有進行逮捕，也會因為檢查機關取證的不充份而失效<ref>[http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf UNFPA–UNICEF 2012] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf |date=20180316152947 }}, p. 48.</ref>。因此這個計劃在八個國家（吉布提、厄立特里亚、埃塞俄比亚、几内亚、几内亚比绍、肯尼亚、塞内加尔和乌干达）培訓了3011人執行相關法律，並且支援相關宣傳，提昇當地的意識<ref>[http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf UNFPA–UNICEF 2012] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unfpa.org/sites/default/files/pub-pdf/UNICEF-UNFPA%20Joint%20Programme%20AR_final_v14.pdf |date=20180316152947 }}, pp. 12–13.</ref>。

===不執行女陰殘割的國家===

====概述====

{{As of|2013}}為止，在非洲及中東以外的國家，已有33個國家立法禁止女陰殘割<ref name=UNICEF2013p8>[http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf UNICEF 2013] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/files/FGCM_Lo_res.pdf |date=20150405083031 }}, p. 8.</ref>。女陰殘割由移民帶入澳洲、紐西蘭、歐洲、北美、斯堪地那維亞半島等地；這些地區立法禁止女陰殘割<!--either entirely or from being performed on minors-->{{efn|UNICEF 2005: "Beyond economic factors, migratory patterns have frequently reflected links established in the colonial past. For instance, citizens from Benin, Chad, Guinea, Mali, Niger and Senegal have often chosen France as their destination, while many Kenyan, Nigerian and Ugandan citizens have migrated to the United Kingdom.<p>"In the 1970s, war, civil unrest and drought in a number of African states, including Eritrea, Ethiopia and Somalia, resulted in an influx of refugees to Western Europe, where some countries, such as Norway and Sweden, had been relatively unaffected by migration up to that point. Beyond Western Europe, Canada and the USA in North America, and Australia and New Zealand in Australasia also host women and children who have been subjected to FGM/C, and are home to others who are at risk of undergoing this procedure."<ref>[http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf UNICEF 2005] {{Wayback|url=http://www.unicef-irc.org/publications/pdf/fgm_eng.pdf |date=20180928122738 }}, p. 4.</ref>}}<ref>Australia: [http://www.ag.gov.au/Publications/Documents/ReviewofAustraliasfemalegenitalmutilationlegalframework/Review%20of%20Australias%20female%20genital%20mutilation%20legal%20framework.pdf "Review of Australia's Female Genital Mutilation Legal Framework"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ag.gov.au/Publications/Documents/ReviewofAustraliasfemalegenitalmutilationlegalframework/Review%20of%20Australias%20female%20genital%20mutilation%20legal%20framework.pdf |date=20160305202920 }}, Attorney General's Department, Government of Australia.<p>
